kendall told me to update but i dont have anything to talk about ...well i guess i do. I was sick the last week ! I watched the Notebook and had a good cry on Valentines Day...yep thats my kind of Valentines day.

We got first at our dance competition on saturday, and i got 2nd in drill down to Ms. Katie McCoy! But woo go Wilsonville people!! the top 3 in Novist was all wilsonvillians..Ricara me and Katie!

MY BIRTHDAY IS NEXT THURSDAY!! remember that people...REMEMBER!

So this week was pretty good! 2nd semester started and we all changed classes...i like my old classes better but oh well, what can yah do. I finally have a class with Kendall tho!! It's grand but we get in trouble, a lot. :-D I also have 1st lunch and practically everyone else has 2nd! at first i thought i would hate it but yesterday i sat with nina kevin and spencer and they are fun to sit with! They make the fact that i dont have becka or kendall much better! I miss Becka...i have 0 classes with her plus shes been sick all week so i havent gotten to see her at all!!!!!! I hope she will be at dance today.

Yesterday was fun!! We danced at the basketball game and that went well and then Nina and I decided that we wanted to go to the "boys night out" thing for 6th graders at Wood and teach them a hip hop dance with Jordan and some other girls on our dance team cuz our brothers were there so I went over to Nina's and we listened to awesome music and talked about...stuff! It was fun. Then we went to Wood and taught the boys the dance (there were some hot college chaperones there i might add) which was quite funny, then they gave us pizza and we left and i got home around 11:30! Slept in till 12 and now i am here...talking to you! Have a great day everyone...Peace!

ahhh finals are so stressful! So far ive seen i got an A in spanish a B in groves and a D+ in bio! that sucks!!!!! im so scared to see what i got in geometry though...oh dear. Tomarrow morning i have dance (ugh) but then i get to go shopping and then kendall and becka are coming to mi casa and we are getting ready for STERLINGS PARTY! yep im pretty excited! This week went by to slow even though we had half days for 3 days..i went to boones ferry and wood on wednsday and saw all my old teachers, that was fun kendall becka matty alex trever and ren were there so we had a grand time w. them! and then tonight i went to the basketball games and sang the national anthem (with the rest of the choir) at the varsity game, we won! hung out with Shannon n Stacey and even though the game was boring..shannon and stacey kept me pretty entertained. i better go to bed cuz i have to get up early tomarrow unfortunately.  see yah all at sterlings party!

wow i am so bad at this livejournal thing!! I'll really try to update more i promise...

So this weekend 42 other Wilsonvillians and I went to All-State Honor Choir in Eugene...it was awesome! Our conductor (Karen Kennedy) was so amazing and funny i learned soo much from her! I had so much fun with Katy Shannon n Megan! We met some pretty nice/hot people lol it was very fun I am definitely trying out again next year :-D

Finals are next week! ahh im so stressed and scared! I have 2 B's currently and im mad about this...good golly ms molly i kinda dont like school. And it doesnt help my schedule next semester kind of sucks.

Dance competition this weekend at Tualitin..COME AND WATCH! it should be good

well i have A LOT of hmk and dance tonight...on a wednsday dang it ! Better be off! gosh i keep sneezing..

hmm havent updated in a while cuz i didnt wanna say stuff i would regret lol....this week has been going well so far. Last week sucked but this week is better. Leaving for All-State on Friday i hope that will be fun

That was the first wedding ive ever been to and she looked soo pretty! My other cousin Carter and some of his friends were there too...they performed at the wedding, Carter is SUCH a good guitar player omg i love listening to him yo! When i first met his friends i thought they were very weird but then i got to talking to them and...yep one of them was still pretty weird, the other one was pretty cool tho. I pretty much hung out with them after the wedding at the hotel till like 3:00 in the morning so i am SOO tired! But haha i love my cousin hes so funny :-) Kendall and Becka called me a lot and i called them a lot so it was good and they ended up talking to Carter for like a half n hour lol i hope they liked him....well i think im gunna go now im to tired to remember much else except i like boys and guitars. bye bye!

We went to see Oceans 12 it was good cept kinda confusing..no hot boys except for the ticket person named Dimitri (sp.?) hes pretty hot and is always there whenever we go! *smiles*

alright so someone left this odd comment on my last entry about picking on jason (not wolf) and i definitely dont know what there talking about..it would be nice if ppl like that actually confronted you instead of leaving anonymous comments ...must be off!

Like Sims 2! heck yes..Kendall came over today and played it with me and my girl got pregant :-) BUT THEN I WAS JUST ABOUT TO HAVE THE BABY AND THE COMPUTER FROZE.! i am so mad i have to do it all over again..oh well i <3 that game. I told her she was crazy and she got even madder at me :-) oh well...i better be off..toodles!

Spiderman!! I <3 it!!

today kinda sucked...mostly cuz of my ass for a spanish teacher mr stillinger....ugh i hate him, he should go buy himself deodorant and live in mexico.

Today in Bio...a kid named..john (a stupid junior) kept shoving this humongous dead spider in a jar at my face and i am terrified of spiders yet he wouldnt stop...so he makes some weird noise and i said "um lets not do that again please.." and David (a stupid sophmore) says "how about you dont scream in class anymore" and i said "how bout u dont shove spiders in my face" and then GWEN....turns around and says "how bout Kelsey shuts up" stupid little bitch..go get voice lessons. Oh well at least i have a reason to be mean to her now.

but yes that was about it...geometry was good as usual degi was...ok ..groves sucked as usual. choir was good and lunch was weird but yeah other then that...yay its winter break and yesterday was beautiful :-)

Have you ever  wondered which hurts the most?


Saying something and wishing you

hadn't? or saying nothing and wishing

you had? I guess the most important

things are the hardest  things to say. Don't be

 afraid to tell someone you love them. If

you do, they might break your heart...if you don't,

you might break theirs. Have you ever decided not

to become a  couple because you were so afraid  of

losing what you already had with that person?

Your heart decides whom it likes and 

whom it doesn't. You can't tell your

heart  what to do.


It does it on its own....when you least

suspect it, or even when you don't want

it  to. Have you ever wanted to love

someone with everything you had, but

that other  person was too afraid to let

you?


Too many of us stay walled up because we are too afraid to care

too  much...for fear that the other person does not care as much, or

even at  all. Have you ever denied your feelings

 for someone because your fear of rejection

was too hard to handle? We tell lies

when we are afraid... afraid of what we

 don't know, afraid of what others will

  think, afraid of what will be found out

about us. But every  time  we tell a lie, the thing we fear grows 

stronger. Life is all about risks and it

requires you to jump. Don't be a person who has to

look back and wonder  what they would have done, or could 

have  had. * What would you do if

every time you fell in love

you had to say  good-bye? *What

would you do if every time you wanted

someone they would never be  there? *What

would you do if your best friend died tomorrow and you

never got to tell them how you felt? (even if it

is that you don't care  anymore)*What would you do if you

loved someone more than ever and you

couldn't have them? *What would you do  if you never got the

chance  to  say I am friends with all of my

family and they know I love them?* People

live, but people die.
